<div class="about-copy">
  <p>
    I work comfortably in the space where product, systems, and engineering
    workflows meet. I am especially drawn to projects where shipping a feature
    is not enough, and the real work also involves organizing decisions,
    context, and tools so the system stays useful as the team grows.
  </p>
  <p>
    Applied AI interests me less as a promise and more as an engineering
    question: where to automate, where to put limits, and how to turn a new
    capability into something a team can use with confidence and without hype.
  </p>
  <p>
    I am looking for teams where building, designing, and thinking about the
    whole system are part of the same job. I like getting into the full
    problem early, contributing from the start, and leaving behind a clearer,
    more maintainable, and more useful foundation than the one I found.
  </p>
</div>

